{
  "texts": [
    "36 have introduced QUEST as a framework for human evaluation of LLMs in healthcare following a comprehensive literature review on the topic.",
    "QUEST includes five principles for human evaluation of LLMs, including Quality of information, Understanding and reasoning, Expression style and persona, Safety and harm, and Trust and confidence.",
    "Multiple benchmarks have been proposed to evaluate model summarisation capabilities in the biomedical domain, including over biomedical literature [37] [38] [39] [40], medical forum conversations 41, and radiology reports 22, 42.",
    "However, these benchmarks do not capture the nuances of patient-facing clinical interactions, where LLM-documentation holds most promise.",
    "Recently, Umapathi et al."
  ]
}